				"synopsis": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "Locke and Marricko confront Kagha - the person responsible for the death of their daughter. In the first scenarion, Kagha is sincerely remorseful for her actions. She begs for forgiveness.\r\n\r\nIn the second, she is cold and unrepentant. She thinks the parents are all bluster and will not harm her (spoiler - she's very wrong.)"
